reviews.text: Reasonably nice looking, however the new departure screens were not working and no announcements were playing out of the new speakers.

Unmanned station with no ticket machine or information updates regarding trains is the only drawback - it is clear to which platform you need for travelling - there is a timetable on a poster - it is a pleasant station and easily accessible if you are doing the Pennine Way, but it is  a 5 minute walk to the town, it is remote

No ticket machine, no ticket booth. Conductor on the train decided that he would not offer me a ticket and instead continued to explain that I was expected to pay a fine yet there was no option or opportunity for me to purchase a ticket.
A Lovely railway station on the Little North Western Railway. Steam trains pass through regularly.
A platform number or a sign advising of which side to wait at would be great help.
